items.text: I loved the salad covered with smoked salmon. Large coffee cup. Limited seats if go on weekends unless go before 12 noon. Price above average. Burgers good..
so I recently said that the coffee is overpriced. I take it back because for the size they serve, I'd say the price is decent.
Cosy place with decent food and coffee. Especially with no service charge, willl come again.
The iced mocha is diluted but their food is quite nice. Had Caesar Salad and apple crumble
The coffee is very strong. Piccolo is slightly sour for my liking but they serve good food here!
Umami Prawn Capellini. Best. Come on Thursdays for their promotional pasta 1-for-1
Terrible service. Barista needs an attitude check. My friend sent her coffee back twice. One of the worst Eggs Benny I've had in SG - rubbery, over cooked eggs, tasteless hollandaise  & soggy muffin.
Nice place for lunch. The blue cheese burger is worth trying
Apple crumble tested and approved
OMG burger was good value. Unami pasta was however nothing to rave about. Sufficient space for indoor and outdoor dining.
Coffee is great!! I find the usual latte a little too milky so ask for it to be filled 3/4. Perfect!! Also highly recommend the umami prawn. Delish!

Okay, here's the thing. Food and drink are good but kitchen and service are so unreliable that going here for anything more complicated than a coffee is a bit like playing Russian roulette. I'll pass.
Only had the coffee here. It's ok.
Agree with Jennifer. Pancakes ain't great at all. Eggs Benedict so so too.
Expensive and hard to find a seat but nice industrial atmosphere
Umami Prawn Capellini is most awesome!! Yummmm
OMG Burger is very good: great meat, proper bacon and egg, really juicy. May be the best burger in town.
The OMG burger is rather satisfying.
Kinda sad that the food standard is declining while prices are on the up. Service Charge + GST have finally kicked in so it's not really worth anyone's time
Love the Umami Prawn and Watermelon dessert
Giant cups! Compared to other cafes. My OMG Burger was legit, pretty good! ^_−☆
Chili crab pasta is recommended!
Umami prawn capellini & the OMG burger are awesome!
Great brunch spot with free wifi 👍🏼
Try the Ricotta pancakes!
Very nice mushroom tagliatelle! Nice staff and good Wifi too!
Food and alcohol good (miso pork, omg burger) but questionable service-they kept mixing up orders,  missing out orders n needs to be asked 2 clear tables n 4 water. Slow too. All toilets choked up
All day happy hour: 1-for-1 for all house pours @ $10/glass.
Panseared watermelon steaks with balsamic vinegratte topped with lemon sorbet. Interesting dessert although I thought it is more of a starter
Coffee is pretty good but if you, like me, are not a fan of overly sweet stuff you may want to avoid the burgers on brioche buns.
For Brunch, after 11 am is the best cause you'll get a wider selection. On another note having ONG burger for brunch will last you through the day if it can all fit!
Upstairs sofa is so cozy that you may sleep soon. Will go back.
OMG burger is da bomb.
The Umami prawn capellini and Angus Tenderloin were very good. Nice coffee.
Love sitting outside with the fantastic music playing. The deconstructed apple crumble is wonderful and so is my iced mocha.
Coffee was okay only but food was good. We had the egg ben and croque monsieur. Poached eggs were runny enough and the bacon in the egg ben was very crispy! Will be back to try the pasta and burger!
Friendly staffs, good quantity food! 😁😁 there's also a stamp card .. After having 9 drinks u get the 10th for free!
Gibraltar and siphon coffee are fantastic.
Prawn cappeline is power!! Unique taste of seaweed + fish roe + aglio olio 👍
Really nice place for brunch. Good coffee and cozy settings!
Decent  but overpriced coffee. A little bit too milky but fragrant. Mild acidity coffee with blend aftertaste. (Iced latte)
Great coffee and friendly staff.
When your customer (friend I'm dining with) says that he doesn't smell the truffle in the truffle fries... Don't insist that there's truffle oil in it.  Service needs improvement:
Brilliant range of roasts! Shame mains are often a little too rich.
OMG Burger,  Foie Gras Mushroom Risotto and Coffee are... jewels.
Ang Peng Siong, once ranked as the world's fastest swimmer, is a regular here. I saw him on my two visits here. :)
Good brunch spot in Farrer Park. Food on the menu is generally quite good. I'd recommend the fish tacos, eggs benedict and the foie gras risotto.
Stay away from the tiramisu like your life depended on it.
Horrible, low quality food. Bad coffee.Nothing healthy. Feels like Starbucks.
I usually love the service of the staff here...not today. The lady at the counter looks as if we harassed her.
Try the amazing Ricotta pancakes or the simple but satisfying croque monsieur. I love the music here, soft Pearl Jam and Nirvana songs are played...so perfect.

Jewel is the most dependable group of cafes for specialty coffee in the city. As with all locations this branch has the usual attractive interior and knowledgeable staff preparing excellent pour over.
Scotch egg is interesting ;)
Good coffee and burger was nice
OpeOperation hours:Mon - Thurs: 9am - 10pmFri & Sat: 9am - 12mn
I like the egg benedict wkend brunch (till3pm) and apple crumble
Nice place to chillout. Love the prawn pasta, and apple crumble dessert!
Gibraltar (piccolo latte), burgers, breakfast, truffle mushroom soup, syphon coffee

Burgers: Looks promising w Broiche bun & home-made patty. Ate OMG! burger. Layered w slices of luncheon meat & bacon. According 2 staff, we were d 1st 2 eat w/o using utensils. Dat's how yummy it was!
The OMG burger is a delicious mess, the apple crumble is damn delectable, the music is quite good, and the ambiance is artsy and relaxed.
Cocktails: Stick w their coffee & food. Ordered a few variety. All tasted watered down, w/o any alco kick :-(
The savory beef patty combined with the sweetness of the bacon jam, zestiness of the Granny Smiths, and cheesy goodness of the, well, cheese.. is pure gold. Praise the Lard indeed!
Unique dessert n big cup coffee. Dessert is just watermelon, sorbet with  balsamic sauce .
Got here and asked for a seat upstairs but was told that upstairs was for reservations only. The wifi sucks, awfully low signal. A couple came in later and got seated upstairs without reservations.
The atmospheric place.Friendly staff. Clean toilet!Well cooked Truffle Fries-10$,good coffee on soy milk, also i liked SmokedSalmonSalad-12$.But pastas & chicken are mediocre.Average bill is 50$
Food is pretty good. I've tried a few breakfast items and burgers. A bit pricey. Coffee is acidic/sour. They have outdoor seating.
Iberico pork: Cooked half-pink, it was d perfect way to eat this delicious Spanish meat. There wasn't enuf left for me after passing it ard d table!
coffee is great but expensive. $6/cup. more pics at http://www.eatprayflying.com/cafe-review-jewel-cafe-and-bar/
Coffee is expensive. It's not crazy good coffee, but better than Starbucks IMHO. Ricotta pancake wasn't that great. Don't know why ppl rave about it. The croque Madame is good but needs more bechamel
Foie Gras Mushroom Risotto - good, fresh and juicy mushrooms, creamy rich flavour. Rice grains are a tad undercooked though, it should be cooked longer and more evenly.
Free Wifi password: singleorigin.
Casual cafe good for gathering with friends over lunch: fish and chips, risotto. Stay for coffee as the place is comfortable.
pan-seared watermelon steak dessert! with pineapple sorbet & balsamic glaze.. very interesting taste!
Variety of coffee available and decent burgers which are actually cooked medium (unlike most places in Singapore at the moment). Truffle fries are a plus!
Awesome mocha!
